metadata:

hadiths[107]{hadithnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
3550,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) prayed in a Khamisah* that had markings on it. Then he said: ‘These markings distracted me. Take it to Abu Jahm and bring me an Anbijaniyyah.’”",32,1,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ایک چادر میں نماز پڑھی ,3550,
3551,"It was narrated that Abu Burdah said:“I entered upon ‘Aishah and she brought out to me a thick waist wrap of the type made in Yemen, and one of these cloaks that are called Mulabbadah,* and she swore to me that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) had passed away in them.”",32,2,,,,,,ابوبردہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کی خدمت میں حاضر ہوا، انہوں نے,3551,
3552,It was narrated from ‘Ubadah bin Samit that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) prayed in a Shamlah tied with a knot,32,3,,,,,,عبادہ بن صامت رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ایک ایسی چادر میں نماز پڑ,3552,
3553,"It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:“I was with the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) and over him was a Najrani upper wrap with a thick border.”",32,4,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں  کہ میں نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے ساتھ تھا، آپ کے جسم پر موٹے,3553,
3554,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“I never saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) insulting anyone, and no garment was ever folded up for him.”",32,5,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  میں نے کبھی رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو نہیں دیکھا ,3554,
3555,"It was narrated from Sahl bin Sa’d Sa’idi that a woman came to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) with a woven sheet – he said:* “What type of woven sheet?” He said: “A Shamlah.” She said: “O Messenger of Allah, I have woven this with my own hands for you to wear.” The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) took it, since he needed it. He came out to us wearing it as a lower wrap. So-and-so the son of so-and-so.” – a man whose name he told that day – said: “O Messenger of Allah, how beautiful this sheet is! Let me wear it.” He said: “Yes.” When he went inside he folded it up and sent it to him. The people said to him: “By Allah, you have not done well. The Prophet (ﷺ) wore it because he needed it, then you asked for it, and you knew that he would not refuse anyone who asked him for something.” He said: “By Allah, I did not ask for it so that I could wear it, rather I asked for it so that it could be my shroud.” Sahl said: “And it became his shroud the day he died.”",32,6,,,,,,سہل بن سعد ساعدی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  ایک عورت رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی خدمت میں «برد,3555,
3556,"It was narrated that Anas said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) wore wool and sandals, and he wore coarse, rough garments.”",32,7,,,,,,انس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے اون کا  ( سادہ اور موٹا )  لباس پہنا ہ,3556,
3557,"It was narrated that Abu Umamah said:“Umar bin Khattab put on a new garment and said: Al-hamdu lillahil-ladhi kasani ma uwari bihi ‘awrati, wa atajammalu bihi fi hayati (Praise is to Allah Who has clothed me in something with which I conceal my nakedness and adorn myself in my life). Then he said: ‘I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) say: “Whoever puts on a new garment and says: Al-hamdu lillahil- ladhi kasani ma uwari bihi ‘awrati, wa atajammalu bihi fi hayati (Praise be to Allah Who has clothed me in something with which I conceal my nakedness and adorn myself in my life), then takes the garment that has worn out, or that he had taken off and gives it in charity, he will be under the shelter, protection and care of Allah, whether he lives or dies.’ He said this three times.”",32,8,,,,,,"ابوامامہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ نے نیا کپڑا پہنا تو یہ دعا پڑھی: «الحمد ",3557,
3558,"It was narrated from Ibn `Umar that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) saw `Umar wearing a white shirt and he said:“Is this garment of yours washed or a new one?” He said: “Rather it has been washed.” He said: “Ilbas jadida, wa `ish hamida, wa mut shahida (May you wear new clothes, live a good life and die as martyr).”",32,9,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے عمر رضی اللہ عنہ کو ای,3558,
3559,"It was narrated from Abu Sa’eed Al-Khudri that the Prophet (ﷺ) forbade two kinds of dress. Those two types of dress are Ishtimalus- Samma’* and Ihtiba’ in a single garment, with no part of it upon his private part",32,10,,,,,,ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے دو طرح کے پہناوے سے منع فر,3559,
3560,"It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade two kinds of dress:Ishtimalus-Samma’ and Ihtiba’, exposing one’s private part to the sky",32,11,,,,,,ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے دو طرح کے پہناوے سے منع فرمایا,3560,
3561,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade two kinds of dress: Ishtimalus-Samma’ and Ihtiba’ in one garment, when you are exposing your private part to the sky.”",32,12,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے دو طرح کے پہناوے سے منع,3561,
3562,"It was narrated from Abu Burdah that his father said to him:“O my son, if only you could have seen us when we were with the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), when rain fell on us; you would have thought that we smelled like sheep.”",32,13,,,,,,"ابوبردہ اپنے والد ابوموسیٰ اشعری سے روایت کرتے ہیں کہ  میرے والد نے مجھ سے کہا: میرے بیٹے! کاش تم ہم",3562,
3563,"It was narrated that ‘Ubadah bin Samit said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) came out to us one day, wearing a Roman cloak of wool with narrow sleeves. He led us in prayer wearing that, and nothing else.”",32,14,,,,,,عبادہ بن صامت رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ایک دن رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم اون کا بنا ہوا تنگ آستی,3563,
3564,"It was narrated from Salman Farisi that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) performed ablution, then he turned his woolen cloak that he was wearing inside out and wiped his face with it",32,15,,,,,,سلمان فارسی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے وضو فرمایا، پھر اون والے جب,3564,
3565,"It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:“I saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) marking sheep on their ears, and I saw him wearing a cloak around his wrist.”",32,16,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو بکریوں کے کانوں میں داغ,3565,
3566,"It was narrated from Ibn ‘Abbas that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“The best of your garments are the white ones, so wear them and shroud your dead in them.”",32,17,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  تمہارے بہترین ک",3566,
3567,"It was narrated from Samurah bin Jundab that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“Wear white garments, for they are purer and better.”",32,18,,,,,,"سمرہ بن جندب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  سفید کپڑے پہنو کہ یہ",3567,
3568,"It was narrated from Abu Darda’ that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“The best of that in which you visit Allah in your graves and your mosque is white (garments).”",32,19,,,,,,"ابوالدرداء رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  سب سے بہتر لباس جس کو ",3568,
3569,"It was narrated from Ibn ‘Umar that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“Whoever lets his garment drag out of pride, Allah will not look at him on the Day of Resurrection.”",32,20,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو اپنے کپڑے ",3569,
3570,"It was narrated from ‘Atiyyah, that Abu Sa’eed said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘Whoever lets his lower wrap drag out of pride, Allah will not look at him on the Day of Resurrection.” He ( ‘Atiyyah) said ""I met Ibn 'Umar in Al-Balaat so I mentioned Abu Sa'eed's hadith from the Prophet (ﷺ). So he said and pointed to his ears 'My two ears heard it, and my heart preserved it",32,21,,,,,,"ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس نے غرور و تکبر س",3570,
3571,"It was narrated that a young man of Quriash passed by Abu Hurairah with his cloak dragging. He said:“O my nephew! I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) saying ‘Whoever let his garment drag out of pride, Allah will not look at him on the Day of Resurrection.’”",32,22,,,,,,ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ان کے پاس سے قریش کا ایک جوان اپنی چادر لٹکائے ہوئے گزرا، آپ نے ا,3571,
3572,"It was narrated that Hudhaifah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) took hold of the lower part of my calf or his calf and said: ‘This is where the lower wrap should come to. If you insist, then lower, and if you insist, then lower, but the lower wrap has no right to (come to) the ankle.’”",32,23,,,,,,حذیفہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے میری پنڈلی کے نیچے کا پٹھا پکڑا اور ,3572,
3573,"It was narrated from ‘Ala bin ‘Abdur-Rahman that his father said:“I said to Abu Sa’eed: ‘Did you hear anything from the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) concerning the lower wrap?’ He said: ‘Yes. I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) say: ‘The lower wrap of the believer should come to mid-calf, but there is no sin on him if it comes between that point and the ankle. But whatever is lower than the ankle is in the Fire.’ And he said three times: ‘Allah will not look at the one who lets his lower wrap drag out of vanity.’”",32,24,,,,,,"عبدالرحمٰن کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ سے کہا: کیا آپ نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ ",3573,
3574,"It was narrated from Mughirah bin Shu’bah that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“O Sufyan bin Sahl, do not let your garment hang, for Allah does not like those who let their garments hang below the ankles.’”",32,25,,,,,,"مغیرہ بن شعبہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  سفیان بن سہل!  ( ٹخ",3574,
3575,"It was narrated that Umm Salamah said:There was no garment more beloved to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) than the shirt.”",32,26,,,,,,ام المؤمنین ام سلمہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو کرتے  ( قمیص )  سے بڑ,3575,
3576,"It was narrated from Salim, from his father, that the Prophet (ﷺ) said:“Hanging down may apply to the waist wrap, shirt or turban. Whoever lets any of these drag out of pride, Allah will not look at him on the Day of Resurrection.”",32,27,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:   «اسبال»: تہبند،",3576,
3577,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Abbas said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to wear a shirt that was short in the sleeves and length.”",32,28,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ایسی قمیص پہنتے جس کی آستی,3577,
3578,"Mu’awiyah bin Qurrah narrated that his father said:“I came to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) and gave him my pledge, and the buttons of his shirt were undone.”",32,29,,,,,,قرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاس آیا اور آپ سے بیعت کی، اس وقت,3578,
3579,"It was narrated that Suwaid bin Qais said:“The Prophet (ﷺ) came to us and haggled with us over the price of trousers.”",32,30,,,,,,سوید بن قیس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ہمارے پاس نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم تشریف لائے تو آپ نے ہم س,3579,
3580,"It was narrated that Umm Salamah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) was asked about how long a woman’s hem should hang down. He said: ‘A hand span.’ I said: ‘But then (her legs and feet) will be uncovered.’ He said: ‘Then a forearm’s length, but no more than that.’”",32,31,,,,,,"ام المؤمنین ام سلمہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے سوال کیا گیا: عورت اپ",3580,
3581,"It was narrated from Ibn ‘Umar:“The wives of the Prophet (ﷺ) were allowed to let their hems hang down, so they used to come to us and we would measure one forearms length for them with a reed.”",32,32,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی ازواج مطہرات رضی اللہ ع,3581,
3582,"It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that the Prophet (ﷺ) said to Fatimah, or to Umm Salamah:“Let your hem down one forearm’s length.”",32,33,,,,,,ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فاطمہ یا ام سلمہ رضی اللہ عنہا ,3582,
3583,"It was narrated from ‘Aishah that the Prophet (ﷺ) said, concerning how long a woman’s hem should hang down:“A hand span.” ‘Aishah said: “This may show her calves.” He said: “Then a forearm’s length.”",32,34,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے عورتوں کے دامن کے سلس,3583,
3584,"It was narrated from Ja’far bin ‘Amr bin Huraith that his father said:“I saw the Prophet (ﷺ) delivering a sermon on the pulpit, wearing a black turban.”",32,35,,,,,,عمرو بن حریث رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو منبر پر خطبہ دیتے دیکھا,3584,
3585,It was narrated from Jabir that the Prophet (ﷺ) entered Makkah wearing a black turban,32,36,,,,,,جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم جب مکہ میں  ( فتح کے دن )  داخل ہوئے، ,3585,
3586,"It was narrated from Ibn ‘Umar that the Prophet (ﷺ) entered (Makkah), on the Day of the Conquest of Makkah, wearing a black turban",32,37,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم فتح مکہ کے دن مکہ میں داخل,3586,
3587,"Ja’far bin ‘Amr bin Huraith narrated that his father said:“It is as if I can see the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), wearing a black turban, with the ends hanging down his shoulders.”",32,38,,,,,,عمرو بن حریث رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  گویا میں رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو دیکھ رہا ہوں، اور آ,3587,
3588,"It was narrated from Anas bin Malik that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“Whoever wears silk in this world will not wear it in the Hereafter.”",32,39,,,,,,"انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس آدمی نے دنیا میں ",3588,
3589,"It was narrated that Bara’ bin ‘Azib said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade brocade, silk, and embroidered brocade.”",32,40,,,,,,براء رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے  ( مردوں کے لیے )  دیباج، حریر اور اس,3589,
3590,"It was narrated that Hudhaifah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade wearing silk and gold. He said: ‘They are for them in this world and for us in the Hereafter.’”",32,41,,,,,,حذیفہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے  ( مردوں کے لیے )  ریشم اور سونا پہن,3590,
3591,"It was narrated from ‘Abdullah bin ‘Umar that ‘Umar bin Khattab saw a silken two piece suit (being offered for sale). He said:“O Messenger of Allah, why don’t you buy this two piece suit (to wear for meeting) the delegations, and on Fridays?” The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: “This is only worn by one who has no share in the Hereafter.”",32,42,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ نے ریشم کا ایک سرخ جوڑا دیکھا تو,3591,
3592,"It was narrated from Anas bin Malik that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) granted a concession to Zubair bin ‘Awwam and ‘Abdur-Rahman bin ‘Auf, allowing them to wear silk shirts, because of a rash they were suffering from",32,43,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے زبیر بن عوام اور عبدالرحمٰن بن,3592,
3593,"It was narrated from ‘Umar that he used to forbid silk and brocade, except for what was like this:Then he gestured with his finger, then a second, and a third, and a fourth (i.e., the width of four fingers), and he said: “The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to forbid it.”",32,44,,,,,,عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  وہ خالص ریشمی کپڑے  ( حریر و دیباج )  کے استعمال سے منع فرماتے تھے ,3593,
3594,"It was narrated that Abu ‘Umar, the freed slave of Asma’, said:“I saw Ibn ‘Umar buying a turban that had some markings, then he called for a pair of scissors and cut that off. I entered upon Asma’ and mentioned that to her, and she said: ‘May ‘Abdullah perish, O girl! Give me the garment of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ).’ A garment was brought that was hemmed with brocade on the sleeves, necklines and openings (at the front and back).”",32,45,,,,,,اسماء رضی اللہ عنہا کے غلام ابوعمر کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کو دیکھا کہ انہوں نے ا,3594,
3595,"‘Ali bin Abu Talib said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) took hold of some silk in his left hand and some gold in his right, then he raised his hands and said: ‘These two are forbidden for the males of my nation, and permitted to the females.’”",32,46,,,,,,علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے اپنے بائیں ہاتھ میں ریشم ا,3595,
3596,"It was narrated from ‘Ali that a two-piece suit hemmed with silk, either on the wrap or the weft,* was given to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), and he sent them to me (‘Ali). I came to him and said:“O Messenger of Allah, what should I do with these? Shall I wear them?” He said: “No, rather make them into head-cloths and give them to the Fatimahs.”",32,47,,,,,,علی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی خدمت میں ایک ریشمی  ( جوڑا )  تحفہ ,3596,
3597,"It was narrated that ‘Abdullah bin ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) came out to us, and in one of his hands was a garment of silk and in the other was some gold. He said: ‘These are forbidden to the males of my nation and permitted to the females.’”",32,48,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمرو رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ہمارے پاس گھر سے نکل کر آئ,3597,
3598,"It was narrated that Anas said:“I saw Zainab the daughter of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) wearing a shirt of Siyara’ silk",32,49,,,,,,انس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی صاحب زادی زینب رضی اللہ عنہا کو,3598,
3599,"It was narrated that Bara’ said:“I never saw anyone more handsome then the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), with his hair combed, wearing a red two-piece suit.”",32,50,,,,,,براء رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے زیادہ خوبصورت بال جھاڑے اور سن,3599,
3600,"‘Abdullah bin Buraidah narrated that his father told him:I saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) delivering a sermon, and Hasan and Husain came forward, wearing red shirts, stumbling and getting up again. The Prophet (ﷺ) stepped down, picked them up and put them in his lap. Then he said: “Allah and His Messenger have spoken the truth. ‘Your wealth and your children are only a trial.’ [64:15] I saw these two and I could not be patient. Then he resumed his sermon.”",32,51,,,,,,بریدہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو خطبہ دیتے دیکھا، اتنے میں حسن,3600,
3601,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade Al-Mufaddam.”",32,52,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے «مفدم» سے منع کیا ہے، یزی,3601,
3602,"It was narrated that ‘Abdullah bin Hunain said:“I heard ‘Ali say: ‘The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade me – and I do not say that he forbade you – from wearing clothes dyed with safflower.’”",32,53,,,,,,علی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مجھے پیلے رنگ کے کپڑے پہننے سے روکا، م,3602,
3603,"It was narrated from ‘Amr bin Shu’aib, from his father, that his grandfather said:“We came with the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) was Thaniyyat Adhakhir. He turned to me, and I was wearing a thin cloak dyed with safflower, and said: ‘What is this?’ And I realized that he disliked it. I came to my family when they were heating their oven and threw it (in the oven). Then I came to him the following day and he said: ‘O ‘Abdullah, what happened to the thin cloak?’ I told him (what I had done) and he said: ‘Why did you not give it to some of your family to wear, for there is nothing wrong with it for women.’”",32,54,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمرو بن العاص رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  ہم اذاخر ۱؎ کے موڑ سے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ و,3603,
3604,"It was narrated that Qais bin Sa’d said:“The Prophet (ﷺ) came to us and we gave him some water with which to cool down. He bathed, then I brought him a yellow blanket, and I saw the traces of Wars (the yellow dye) on the folds of his stomach.”",32,55,,,,,,قیس بن سعد رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ہمارے پاس نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم تشریف لائے، تو ہم نے آپ ک,3604,
3605,"It was narrated from ‘Amr bin Shu’aib, from his father, that his grandfather said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘Eat and drink, give charity and wear clothes, as long as that does not involve any extravagance or vanity.’”",32,56,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمرو بن العاص رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہعلیہ وسلم  نے فرمایا:  کھاؤ ",3605,
3606,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘Whoever wears a garment of pride and vanity, Allah will clothe him, on the Day of Resurrection, in a garment of humiliation.’”",32,57,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے شہرت ک",3606,
3607,"It was narrated that ‘Abdullah bin ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘Whoever wears a garment of pride and vanity in this world, Allah will clothe him in a garment of humiliation on the Day of Resurrection, then set it ablaze.’”",32,58,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے دنیا م",3607,
3608,"It was narrated from Abu Dharr that the Prophet (ﷺ) said:“Whoever wears a garment of pride and vanity, Allah will turn away from him until he takes it off.”",32,59,,,,,,"ابوذر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے شہرت کی خاطر لباس ",3608,
3609,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Abbas said:“I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) say: ‘Any skin that has been tanned has been purified.’”",32,60,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے سنا:  ہر و",3609,
3610,"It was narrated from Maimunah that he (meaning the Prophet (ﷺ)) passed by a dead sheep belonging to the freed slave woman of Maimunah, that had been given to her in charity. He said:“Why don’t they take its skin and ten it, and make us of it?” They said: “O Messenger of Allah, it is dead meat.”* He said: “It is only unlawful to eat it.”",32,61,,,,,,ام المؤمنین میمونہ رضی اللہ عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ  ان کی ایک لونڈی کو صدقہ کی ایک بکری ملی تھی جو مری ,3610,
3611,"It was narrated that Salman said:“One of the Mothers of the Believers had a sheep that died. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) passed by it and said: ‘It would not have harmed its owners if they had made use of its hide.’”",32,62,,,,,,سلمان رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  امہات المؤمنین میں سے کسی ایک کے پاس ایک بکری تھی جو مر گئی، رسول ال,3611,
3612,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) commanded that use should be made of the skins of dead animals, if they were tanned.”",32,63,,,,,,"ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے حکم فرمایا:  جب مردہ جا",3612,
3613,"It was narrated that ‘Abdullah bin ‘Ukaym said:“There came to us a letter from the Prophet (ﷺ) (saying): ‘No not make use of the untanned skin and sinew of dead animals.’”",32,64,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عکیم کہتے ہیں کہ  ہمارے پاس نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کا مکتوب آیا کہ مردار کی کھال او,3613,
3614,"It was narrated that ‘Abdullah bin ‘Abbas said:“The sandals of the Prophet (ﷺ) had two thongs doubled around their straps.”",32,65,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی جوتیوں کے دو تسمے تھے، جو,3614,
3615,"It was narrated that Anas said:“The sandals of the Prophet (ﷺ) had two thongs.”",32,66,,,,,,انس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی جوتیوں کے دو تسمے تھے۔,3615,
3616,"It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“When anyone of you puts on his sandals, let him start with the right, and when he takes them off, let him start with the left.”",32,67,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب تم میں سے کوئی جوتا پ",3616,
3617,It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said; “None of you should walk in one sandal or in one leather sock. Let him take them both off or walk in both of them.”,32,68,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  کوئی بھی شخص ایک جوتا یا",3617,
3618,"It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade putting on sandals whilst standing.”",32,69,,,,,,ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے کھڑے ہو کر جوتا پہننے سے منع فرما,3618,
3619,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Prophet (ﷺ) forbade putting on sandals whilst standing.”",32,70,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے کھڑے کھڑے جوتا پہننے سے م,3619,
3620,"It was narrated from Ibn Buraidah, from his father, that an-Najashi sent a pair of pure black Khuff as a gift to the Prophet (ﷺ) of, which he wore",32,71,,,,,,بریدہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نجاشی  ( اصحمہ بن بحر )  نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی خدمت ,3620,
3621,"It was narrated that Abu Hurairah attributed to the Prophet (ﷺ):“The Jews and the Christians do not dye (their hair), so differ from them.”",32,72,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  یہود و نصاریٰ خضاب نہی",3621,
3622,"It was narrated from Abu Dharr that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:“The best things with which you change gray hair are henna and Katam.”",32,73,,,,,,"ابوذر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  بالوں کی سفیدی بدلنے کے لیے",3622,
3623,"It was narrated that ‘Uthman bin Mawhab said:“I entered upon Umm Salamah and she brought out for me a hair of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), which was dyed with henna and Katam.”",32,74,,,,,,عثمان بن موہب کہتے ہیں کہ  میں ام المؤمنین ام سلمہ رضی اللہ عنہا کی خدمت میں حاضر ہوا تو انہوں نے رس,3623,
3624,"It was narrated from Jabir that he said:“Abu Quhaifah was brought to the Prophet (ﷺ) on the Day of the Conquest (of Makkah), and his head was all white. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘Take him to some of his womenfolk and let them change this, but avoid black.’”",32,75,,,,,,جابر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  فتح مکہ کے دن ابوقحافہ رضی اللہ عنہ کو نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے,3624,
3625,"It was narrated that Suhaib Al-Khair said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ‘The best thing with which you can dye your hair is this black (dye). It makes your women desire you and creates fear in the hearts of your enemies.’”",32,76,,,,,,"صہیب الخیر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو خضاب تم لگاتے ہو ان",3625,
3626,"It was narrated from Sa’eed bin Abu Sa’eed that ‘Ubaid bin Juraij asked Ibn ‘Umar:“I see that you dye your beard yellow with Wars.” Ibn ‘Umar said: “As for my dyeing of my beard yellow with Wars, I saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) dyeing his beard yellow.”",32,77,,,,,,"عبید بن جریج سے روایت ہے کہ  انہوں نے ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے پوچھا: میں آپ کو اپنی داڑھی ورس سے ز",3626,
3627,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Abbas said:“The Prophet (ﷺ) passed by a man who had dyed his hair with henna and said: ‘How handsome this is!’ Then he passed by another who had dyed his hair with henna and Katam, and said: ‘This one is more handsome than that one.’ Then he passed by another who had dyed his hair yellow and said: ‘This one is more handsome than all of them.’”",32,78,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کا گزر ایک ایسے شخص کے پاس ہ,3627,
3628,"It was narrated that Abu Juhaifah said:“I saw the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ), and this part of his hair was white” – meaning the tuft of hair between the lower lip and the chin",32,79,,,,,,ابوحجیفہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے یہ بال یعنی داڑھی بچہ سفید,3628,
3629,"It was narrated that Humaid said:“Anas bin Malik was asked: ‘Did the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) dye his hair?’ He said: ‘He did not have any white hair apart from approximately seventeen or twenty hairs at the front of his beard.’”",32,80,,,,,,"حمید کہتے ہیں کہ  انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے سوال کیا گیا: کیا رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے خضاب",3629,
3630,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The white hair of the Prophet (ﷺ) numbered approximately twenty.”",32,81,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کا بڑھاپا تقریباً ً بیس بال ,3630,
3631,"It was narrated that Mujahid said:“Umm Hani said: ‘When the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) entered Makkah he had four braids.’”",32,82,,,,,,ام ہانی رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم جب مکہ میں  ( فتح کے روز )  داخل ہوئ,3631,
3632,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Abbas said:“The People of the Book used to let their hair hang down, and the idolaters used to part their hair. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) liked to be more like the People of the Book. So the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) let his forelock hang down, then after that he parted it.”",32,83,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  اہل کتاب اپنے بالوں کو پیشانی پر لٹکائے رکھتے تھے، اور م,3632,
3633,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“I used to part the hair of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) behind his crown, and let his forelock hang down.”",32,84,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  میں رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے سر پر چندیا کے پچھل,3633,
3634,"It was narrated that Anas said:“The hair of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) was wavy, and (hung down) between his ears and his shoulders.”",32,85,,,,,,انس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے بال دونوں کانوں اور مونڈھوں کے درمیان ,3634,
3635,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) had hair that came between his earlobes and his shoulders.”",32,86,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے بال مونڈھوں سے اوپر اور,3635,
3636,"It was narrated that Wa’il bin Hujr said:“The Prophet (ﷺ) saw me when I had long hair. He said: ‘Bad news, bad news!’ So I went away and cut it short. Then the Prophet (ﷺ) saw me and said: ‘I did not mean you, but this is better.’”",32,87,,,,,,وائل بن حجر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مجھے دیکھا کہ میرے بال لمبے ہیں,3636,
3637,"It was narrated from Nafi’ that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade Qaza’.” He (Nafi’) said: “What is Qaza’?” He said: “It means shaving part of a child’s head and leaving another part.”",32,88,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے «قزع» سے منع فرمایا۔ راوی,3637,
3638,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade Qaza’.”",32,89,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے «قزع» سے منع فرمایا ہے۔,3638,
3639,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) wore a ring of silver, then he had engraved on it (the words) ‘Muhammad Rasul Allah’ (Muhammad the Messenger of Allah). And he said: ‘No one should have his ring engraved like this ring of mine.’”",32,90,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے چاندی کی ایک انگوٹھی بنوا,3639,
3640,"It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) had a ring made for him, and he said: ‘I have had a ring made for me and had it engraved, and no one should make a ring with similar engraving.’”",32,91,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ایک انگوٹھی بنوائی، اور فرمایا,3640,
3641,"It was narrated from Anas bin Malik that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) wore a ring of silver, in which was an Ethiopian gemstone and the inscription:‘Muhammad Rasul Allah’ (Muhammad the Messenger of Allah).”",32,92,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے چاندی کی ایک انگوٹھی بنوائی,3641,
3642,"It was narrated that ‘Ali said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade wearing gold rings.”",32,93,,,,,,علی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے سونے کی انگوٹھی پہننے سے منع فرمایا۔,3642,
3643,"It was narrated that Ibn ‘Umar said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade gold rings.”",32,94,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے سونے کی انگوٹھی  ( پہننے ,3643,
3644,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah the Mother of the Believers said:“Najashi sent some jewelry as a gift to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ). Among that was a gold ring with an Ethiopian gemstone. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) picked it up with a stick – as if he found it distasteful – or with one of his fingers, then he called for his daughter, Umamah bint Abul-‘As, and said: ‘Wear this, O my daughter.’”",32,95,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  نجاشی نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی خدمت میں ایک چ,3644,
3645,It was narrated from Ibn ‘Umar that the Prophet (ﷺ) used to wear (his ring) with the stone nearest his palm,32,96,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم اپنی انگوٹھی کے نگینے کو ہ,3645,
3646,"It was narrated from Anas bin Malik that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) wore a silver ring with an Ethiopian gemstone, and he used to ear the stone in towards his palm",32,97,,,,,,انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے چاندی کی انگوٹھی پہنی، اس م,3646,
3647,It was narrated from ‘Abdullah bin Ja’far that the Prophet (ﷺ) used to wear a ring on his right hand,32,98,,,,,,عبداللہ بن جعفر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم اپنے داہنے ہاتھ میں انگوٹ,3647,
3648,"It was narrated that ‘Ali said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade me to wear a ring on this and on this,” meaning the little finger and the thumb",32,99,,,,,,علی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مجھے منع فرمایا کہ میں اس میں اور اس م,3648,
3649,"It was narrated from Abu Talhah that the Prophet (ﷺ) said:“The angels do not enter a house in which there is a dog or an image.”",32,100,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  ابوطلحہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ نبی اکرم صلی اللہ عل,3649,
3650,"It was narrated from ‘Ali bin Abu Talib that the Prophet (ﷺ) said:“The angels do not enter a house in which there is a dog or an image.”",32,101,,,,,,"علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  فرشتے اس گھر میں د",3650,
3651,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“Jibril (as) promised the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) that he would come to him at a certain hour, but he was late. The Prophet (ﷺ) went out and there was Jibril standing at the door. He said: ‘What kept you from entering?’ He said: ‘There is a dog in the house, and we do not enter a house in which there is a dog or an image.’”",32,102,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  جبرائیل علیہ السلام نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے ,3651,
3652,"It was narrated from Abu Umamah that a woman came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and told him that her husband was away on some military campaign. She asked him for permission to make an image of a palm tree in her house, and he did not let her, or he forbade her",32,103,,,,,,ابوامامہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  ایک عورت نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاس آ کر آپ کو بتا,3652,
3653,"It was narrated that ‘Aishah said:“I covered a small room closet of mine, meaning, from the inside, with a curtain on which there were images. When the Prophet (ﷺ) came, he tore it down, so I made two pillows from it, and I saw the Prophet (ﷺ) reclining on one of them.”",32,104,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  میں نے اپنے روشن دان پر پردہ ڈالا یعنی اندر سے، پردے می,3653,
3654,"It was narrated that ‘Ali said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) forbade rings of gold and Al-Mitharah,”* meaning the red ones",32,105,,,,,,علی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے سونے کی انگوٹھی پہننے اور گدے استعمال ,3654,
3655,"It was narrated that ‘Amir Al-Hajri said:“I heard Abu Raihanah, the Companion of the Prophet (ﷺ) say: ‘The Prophet (ﷺ) used to forbid riding on leopard skins.’”",32,106,,,,,,ابوریحانہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم چیتوں کی کھال پر سواری کرنے سے منع ف,3655,
3656,"It was narrated that Mu’awiyah said:“The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) used to forbid riding on leopard skins.”",32,107,,,,,,معاویہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم چیتوں کی کھال پر سواری کرنے سے منع فرم,3656,
